A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Wide Area Surveillance (WAS) consists of two complementary advanced sensor systems, the Stateside Affordable Radar System (STARS) and Scorpion. Based on
existing technological capabilities, WAS detects/tracks low, slow and other asymmetrical threats in the airspace and meets the user needs by sensing stressing airborne
targets in complex environments with affordable sensors. The sensor outputs are incorporated into the Battle Control Systems-Fixed (BCS-F) air picture and utilized
as the North American Aerospace Defense Command/ Northern Command (NORAD/NORTHCOM) Command and Control (C2) air surveillance system of record. This
effort is for a S1 Block 2 for the STARS system.

 This program element may include necessary civilian pay expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver Wide Area Surveillance capability. The use of such
 program funds would be in addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in program element 0605827F, 0605828F, 0605829F, 0605831F, 0605832F, 0605833F,
