A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Mission Risk Analysis project encompasses one continuous effort to support the Department of the Air Force (DAF) and Department of War acquisition community.
It enables the Cyber Resiliency Office for Weapon Systems (CROWS) to be the sole-organization to collect and analyze weapon system data from multiple sources
(ex. Program Executive Office portfolios and test and evaluation efforts) to understand the DAF's cyber vulnerability landscape and mitigation initiatives to inform senior
leader resource investment strategies. Additionally, this effort informs efforts in the other CROWS projects to prioritize research and investments to solve enterprise
cyber vulnerability and mitigation needs.

This program element included all necessary expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver weapon system capability. The use of such program funds would be in
addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in program elements 0605829F, 0605831F, 0605833F, and 0605898F.

