Title: High Speed Propulsion and Advanced Weapon Technologies                                                            14.584       14.998      27.862      0.000       27.862
Description: This activity describes Navy applied research investments to advance the Navy's strategic goals of
the Propulsion and Airframes Research Area within the Kinetic Systems Focus Area. These projects support the
development of vehicle, propulsion, and energetic material technologies for high-speed propulsion and advanced
weapon systems. The goal is to develop enabling technologies along with the workforce needed to support
the development of real-time adaptive hypersonic weapon systems that balance unmatched range, speed,
survivability, and precision with stringent size, weight, power, and cost (SWaP-C) requirements and platform
integration constraints.

FY 2026 Plans:
Continuing:
- Development and characterization of ultra-high temperature metamaterials and structures to enable, sensing,
flow control, power generation, and improved aero-thermo-mechanical performance of aeroshells and high-
speed propulsion systems.
- Development of efficient, predictive computational tools for high-speed, air-breathing propulsion systems to
enable robust digital-engineering methodologies.
- Experimental and numerical investigation on the combustion characteristics of solid fuels in supersonic
combustors.


